<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870227-0160 </DOCNO><HL> Mesa Partnership to BanSmoking at Headquarters</HL><DD> 02/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MLPFOOD andamp; BEVERAGE, HOUSEHOLD GOODS, SUPERMARKETS, TOBACCO (FAB) </IN><DATELINE> AMARILLO, Texas  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mesa Limited Partnership banned smoking at its corporate headquarters as of July 1.    About 400 employees work at the oil and natural gas investment partnership's headquarters. The company said it is sponsoring stop-smoking classes for employees and their spouses.    Mesa said it is implementing the policy primarily to benefit those employees who don't smoke. The company, which also operates a fitness center next to the headquarters for its employees, said the ban is an extension of its fitness program. </TEXT></DOC>